<?xml version="1.0"?>
<rdf:RDF xmlns="http://www.semanticweb.org/nab93/ontologies/2026/4/untitled-ontology-2/"
     xml:base="http://www.semanticweb.org/nab93/ontologies/2026/4/untitled-ontology-2/"
     xmlns:owl="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#"
     xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#"
     xmlns:xml="http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace"
     xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#"
     xmlns:rdfs="http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#">
    <owl:Ontology rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core">
        <rdfs:comment>Reasoner-verified consistent, no unsatisfiable classes (HermiT via owlready2, 2026-06-04; includes the referent-typed Inscription subclasses, the carriedBy realization axiom, the B2-referential depth GCI, the FitnessCriterion slot, the SigmaInterventionClass taxonomy — second on-demand Q3 promotion, AGORA n ETHOS intersection, the inter-Sigma coupledTo relation — third on-demand Q3 promotion, AGORA n ATLAS intersection; the PathologicalAttractor class — fourth on-demand Q3 promotion, POLARIS n ETHOS n ATLAS n NEXUS; and AdjacentPossibleConstraint — fifth Sigma-intervention operator, fifth on-demand Q3 promotion, ATLAS n NEXUS; the CollectiveManifoldUpdate operator — sixth on-demand Q3 promotion, AGORA n ATLAS intersection, 2026-06-18; and the AdjacentPossibleMeasure — seventh on-demand Q3 promotion, NEXUS n ETHOS intersection, 2026-06-18; and the DoctrinalRegion class + doctrinallyComposesFrom relation — eighth on-demand Q3 promotion, ETHOS n NEXUS intersection, 2026-06-21, the derived B3 community fibration / region R(C), a structure over B3 that never re-types it). Reproduce: scripts/score_reason.py. All impl layers (core+polaris, core+ethos, core+agora, core+atlas, core+nexus, core+bac) re-verified 2026-06-21 (HermiT via owlready2) after the eighth promotion: all consistent, no unsatisfiable classes. The extension peer core+inscription-market (added 2026-06-29) is auto-discovered by score_reason.py and also verifies consistent with no unsatisfiable classes, so all seven implementation layers (six domain-specific refinements plus the extension peer) satisfy the core-⊕-impl reasoner-conformance check.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Ontology>
    


