    <!-- ── Inter-Sigma coupling (Q3 PROMOTE, 2026-06-04, third on-demand event) ──
         The inter-Sigma-actor coupling relation, long "undefined" (SigmaActorArchitecture S 2),
         resolved by the ATLAS exercise (S 2a) and promoted on the AGORA n ATLAS intersection:
         AGORA uses it implicitly (Level-0 state -> Level-1 alliance cascade, HighCentralityDisruption);
         ATLAS uses it constitutively (a deterrence basin is a dense region of coupledTo). The
         three sub-properties are the three coupling layers; they operate simultaneously on
         different timescales (NAryDeterrence). The Erdos-Renyi density threshold at which a
         Sigma-HOA (coalition / deterrence basin) crystallizes, and the layer-superposition
         weighting, are DL-inexpressible and carried in SigmaActorArchitecture.md S 2a. -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#coupledTo -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#coupledTo">
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#SigmaActor"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#SigmaActor"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#SymmetricProperty"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Multi-layer inter-Sigma-actor coupling. Density over this relation determines Sigma-HOA (coalition / alliance / deterrence basin) crystallization at the same Erdos-Renyi threshold that governs A-actor HOA formation (SO is ER at every stratum). Symmetric: coupling is a mutual relation. Modulated informally by executive-to-executive A-actor relationships (SigmaActorArchitecture S 2).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#coupledByTreaty -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#coupledByTreaty">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#coupledTo"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Treaty layer: formal B3 commitment (alliance, trade agreement, security guarantee); slow, externally legible; strength proportional to commitment specificity and credibility.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#coupledByBehavior -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#coupledByBehavior">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#coupledTo"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Behavioral layer: repeated interaction (trade flows, diplomatic contact, military coordination); medium timescale; strength proportional to interaction frequency and mutual dependence.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#coupledByManifoldProximity -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#coupledByManifoldProximity">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#coupledTo"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Manifold-proximity layer: similarity of effective collective manifolds; the direct analog of the A-actor |phi_i - phi_j|^-1 coupling criterion lifted to the Sigma stratum.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#hasConstituentDomain -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#hasConstituentDomain">
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Node"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Domain"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Links an emergent cycle (Node) to the domain a constituent of its sustaining cycle occupies. Constituent-domain closure: a cycle whose constituents are all B1 is constituent-closed in B1. See ActorTypes / SO-NS-Stratification (constituent-domain closure of emergence cycles) and formal/Formal/Score/Core.lean.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>



    <!-- ── Doctrinal composition + region (Q3 PROMOTE, 2026-06-21, eighth on-demand event) ──
         The B3xB3->B3 doctrinal-composition relation and the community region R(C) it carries —
         the formal home of "a community's shared B3" (the derived B3 community fibration). Promoted
         on the ETHOS n NEXUS intersection: ETHOS as the citation/derivation corpus
         (ethos:DisciplinaryCorpus over ethos:cites), NEXUS as the patent-citation paradigm cluster
         (nexus:ParadigmCluster over nexus:patentCites). A DERIVED construct over the single B3 — NOT a
         re-typing of B3_Inscription and NOT a re-indexing of the primitive (which stays a shared
         singleton, load-bearing for the morphism round-trip). Only the transitivity is DL-expressible;
         the grading-monotonicity, the down-closure of a region, and the graded-product geometry are
         DL-inexpressible — see formal/Formal/Score/Core.lean (DoctrinalNetwork, grade_mono_le,
         region_substrate_closed_and_graded, downClosure_isRegion) and B3RegionGeometry.md. -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#doctrinallyComposesFrom -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#doctrinallyComposesFrom">
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#B3_Inscription"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#B3_Inscription"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#TransitiveProperty"/>
        <rdfs:comment>The B3xB3->B3 doctrinal-composition relation: `y doctrinallyComposesFrom x` means B3 content y composes from / builds on / cites substrate x (a ruling from precedent, a theorem from its lemmas, a paper from what it cites). Transitive: substrate of substrate is substrate. A community's region (DoctrinalRegion) is a down-set of this relation; that down-closure and the emergence-hierarchy grading-monotonicity are DL-inexpressible (Lean S14). Q3 PROMOTE 2026-06-21 (eighth on-demand event, ETHOS n NEXUS).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>



    <!-- ── Trace processing (promote-by-nature, 2026-07-02) ──
         Links a TraceProcessor to the Trace it operates on. See the Trace + open trace-processor
         taxonomy in the Classes section and obsidian/SCORE/measurement/Trace.md. -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#processes -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#processes">
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#TraceProcessor"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Trace"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Links a TraceProcessor to the Trace it operates on.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>



