    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#AAgent -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#AAgent">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Actor"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Class>
                <owl:complementOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#OmegaActor"/>
            </owl:Class>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Class>
                <owl:complementOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#SigmaActor"/>
            </owl:Class>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#Action -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#Action">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Morphism"/>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#Actor -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#Actor">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Node"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#performsMorphism"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Morphism"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:comment>An Actor is a Node whose sustaining cycle operates at least one morphism. Actorhood is graded: a fixed-protocol cluster that operates no morphism of its own is a mechanism, not an actor. The graded boundary is not expressible in OWL; see ActorTypes.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#Node -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#Node">
        <rdfs:comment>An emergent structure sustained by a closed cycle in the coupling graph — the general category. An Actor is the special case of a Node whose cycle operates at least one morphism; a pure-B1 cycle (PureB1Cycle) operates none and is a node, not an actor. NOTE: the upward epistemic horizon (a Node cannot perceive the cycle it constitutes) and bounded agency (downward constraint bounds likelihood, not possibility) are modal/epistemic results, not DL-expressible; see GenerativeMechanism and SO-NS-Stratification in the vault and formal/Formal/Score/Core.lean.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#PureB1Cycle -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#PureB1Cycle">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Node"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#hasConstituentDomain"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#B1_Objective"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#hasConstituentDomain"/>
                <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#B1_Objective"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:comment>A node constituent-closed in B1: every constituent of its sustaining cycle occupies B1. Because operating any morphism requires a B2 or B3 constituent (no intra-B1 morphism), and B1 is disjoint from B2/B3, a PureB1Cycle operates no morphism and is therefore not an Actor — a reasoner derives Actor and PureB1Cycle disjoint.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#B1_Objective -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#B1_Objective">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Domain"/>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#B2_Subjective -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#B2_Subjective">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Domain"/>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#B3_Inscription -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#B3_Inscription">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Domain"/>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#CoInscriptionEvent -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#CoInscriptionEvent"/>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#Domain -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#Domain"/>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#HOA -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#HOA"/>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#HigherOrderAgent -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#HigherOrderAgent">
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#hasHOA"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#HOA"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:comment>Community whose collective dynamics constitute a HOA attractor. The HOA is the community&apos;s emergent basin, not an administrative declaration.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#SelfStabilizationProperty -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#SelfStabilizationProperty">
        <rdfs:comment>An emergent property of a distributed configuration: from every state satisfying a basin predicate, all valid move sequences reach a legitimate state in finite time. Domain-general (a claim about local-rule dynamics on any coupling graph). Orthodoxy anchor: Dijkstra 1974 (Communications of the ACM 17(11), 643–644) — the founding CS paper on distributed control producing global order under purely local rules. Lean: SelfStabilizingWithin, GloballySelfStabilizing (formal/Formal/Score/SelfStabilization.lean). See obsidian/sources/Dijkstra-Edsger.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#WithinBasinConvergence -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#WithinBasinConvergence">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#SelfStabilizationProperty"/>
        <rdfs:comment>SCORE variant of self-stabilization: convergence to legitimate states is guaranteed within a basin, not globally — the conceptual class for the strong-form claim. Applicable where the basin does NOT contain a second stable equilibrium (e.g., non-hysteretic systems). Lean: SelfStabilizingWithin instantiated with a non-trivial Basin. See obsidian/SCORE/emergence/mechanism/Hysteresis.md, obsidian/SCORE/emergence/mechanism/HOA.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#WithinBasinMaintenance -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#WithinBasinMaintenance">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#SelfStabilizationProperty"/>
        <rdfs:comment>SCORE variant of self-stabilization for BISTABLE basins (the SCORE default given hysteresis): from a state that already satisfies the legitimate property and lies in basin, every basin-preserving move sequence preserves the property throughout. Not convergence-from-anywhere (which fails for bistable regions — hysteresis is precisely for admitting a second stable equilibrium in-basin). The autocatalytic-maintenance rule (Hysteresis.md § Aggregate-weight hysteresis) is the load-bearing claim, discharged from axiom to theorem at (B'') via the AutocatalyticFeedback decomposition. Sibling of WithinBasinConvergence, not subclass — the two hold on different topologies of basin. Lean: MaintainedWithinIfPreserved (Score/SelfStabilization.lean); HOAMaintainedWithin, hoaMaintainedWithin (Score/HOAMaintenance.lean). See obsidian/SCORE/emergence/mechanism/HOA.md, obsidian/SCORE/emergence/mechanism/Hysteresis.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#AutocatalyticFeedback -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#AutocatalyticFeedback">
        <rdfs:comment>The decomposition-and-combining mechanism that discharges WithinBasinMaintenance from axiom to theorem: aggregate observable weight = combine(substrate, loop_endowment), with an abstract operator satisfying monotonicity in each argument and closing the hysteresis gap when the loop is engaged. Formalizes only the fast-timescale aggregate-weight mechanism (Hysteresis.md § 3.1); ceiling residue (§ 3.2) and B₃-substrate (§ 3.3) mechanisms remain axiomatic. SCORE does not commit to a specific arithmetic form (Kauffman-multiplicative or Deacon-additive) — the operator is abstract, and canonical additive and multiplicative instances are shipped as options; peers pick one. Lean: AutocatalyticCombine, combineAdditive, combineMultiplicative, hoaPreservedByBasinMove_ifFeedbackEngaged (now a derived theorem), feedbackEngaged (now a derived predicate) (Score/HOAMaintenance.lean). See obsidian/SCORE/emergence/mechanism/AutocatalyticFeedback.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#CeilingResidueProperty -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#CeilingResidueProperty">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#SelfStabilizationProperty"/>
        <rdfs:comment>The Hysteresis.md § 3.2 basin-extension mechanism: Path-A structural manifold-restructuring accumulates as a durable state quantity (ceiling residue) that reduces the effective dissolution threshold. Sibling of WithinBasinMaintenance under SelfStabilizationProperty — the two mechanisms extend maintenance in different ways: WithinBasinMaintenance is preservation within the formal basin under engaged feedback (§ 3.1); CeilingResidueProperty widens the basin below formal dissolution to an effective dissolution set by accumulated residue (§ 3.2, intermediate window width per Hysteresis.md). SCORE does not commit to a specific dependence of effective dissolution on residue — the abstract policy captures the shape (four axioms) with canonical linear and multiplicative instances shipped. NOT formalized at this tier: member turnover (Hysteresis.md flags it erodes ceiling residue), LifeCyclePhases generational renewal, and Path-A residue-accumulation dynamics. Lean: CeilingResiduePolicy, linearCeilingResidue, multiplicativeCeilingResidue, ExtendedBasin, hoaPreservedByExtendedBasinMove_ifFeedbackEngaged (axiom, discharge pending), hoaMaintainedExtended (Score/HOAMaintenance.lean §HM9-HM11). See obsidian/SCORE/emergence/mechanism/CeilingResidue.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#B3SubstrateProsthetic -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#B3SubstrateProsthetic">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#SelfStabilizationProperty"/>
        <rdfs:comment>The Hysteresis.md § 3.3 widest-window basin-extension mechanism: co-inscribed formal B₃ layer (constitution, bylaws, official roles) holds the coupling structure open even when informal networks thin. Sibling of WithinBasinMaintenance (§ 3.1) and CeilingResidueProperty (§ 3.2) under SelfStabilizationProperty — the three mechanisms extend maintenance in different ways with different substrates (B₂ manifold overlap for § 3.2; B₃ formal content for § 3.3). Σ-actor-only (A-actors don't have a formal B₃ layer of their own); handled implicitly via `formalB3Substrate = 0` for A-actors, at which the mechanism becomes vacuous. Distinguishing structural feature vs § 3.2: the "not infinite" constraint (formalized as an irreducibleMinimum axiom) — a formal structure "rejected by all informal networks is paper without power," so effective dissolution can never reach zero. SCORE does not commit to a specific dependence of effective dissolution on formal B₃ substrate — abstract policy with six axioms (the four CeilingResiduePolicy axioms plus irreducibleMinimum_pos and bounded_below_by_irreducible) with canonical linear-floored and multiplicative-floored instances shipped. NOT formalized at this tier: the crossover event (SigmaActorArchitecture § "Lifecycle"), co-inscription dynamics, erosion of formal B₃ under informal-substrate crash, Σ-actor type-level restriction, or composition with § 3.1/§ 3.2 (Hysteresis.md open question #2). Lean: B3SubstratePolicy, linearFlooredB3Substrate, multiplicativeFlooredB3Substrate, FormalExtendedBasin, hoaPreservedByFormalExtendedBasinMove_ifFeedbackEngaged (axiom, discharge pending), hoaMaintainedFormalExtended (Score/HOAMaintenance.lean §HM12-HM14). See obsidian/SCORE/emergence/mechanism/B3SubstrateProsthetic.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#CompositeBasinExtensionProperty -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#CompositeBasinExtensionProperty">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#SelfStabilizationProperty"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Peer-selected composition of § 3.2 (CeilingResidueProperty) and § 3.3 (B3SubstrateProsthetic) into a joint basin extension. Hysteresis.md open question #2 (whether the mechanisms compose additively, multiplicatively, or non-linearly) is GENUINELY OPEN in the vault — this class captures the composition SHAPE (abstract policy with monotonicity axioms and a sanity constraint that the composite must be at least as permissive as either individual mechanism alone) with three peer-selectable canonical instances (min/most-permissive, additive-reductions, multiplicative-factors). Ontological status: composition IS a first-class property of a Σ-actor HOA in principle, but WHICH composition applies is a peer choice, not a SCORE commitment. Lean: CompositeBasinExtensionPolicy, compositeMin, compositeAdditiveReductions, compositeMultiplicativeFactors, CompositelyExtendedBasin, extendedBasin_implies_compositelyExtendedBasin, formalExtendedBasin_implies_compositelyExtendedBasin, hoaPreservedByCompositelyExtendedBasinMove_ifFeedbackEngaged (axiom, discharge depends on settling the composition rule), hoaMaintainedCompositelyExtended (Score/HOAMaintenance.lean §HM15-HM17). See obsidian/SCORE/emergence/mechanism/HysteresisComposition.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#AgentHomogeneityFragility -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#AgentHomogeneityFragility">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#SelfStabilizationProperty"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Dijkstra 1974 "identical machines cannot self-stabilize" applied to SCORE agent populations — the NEGATIVE face (fragility, structural absence) complementing the positive stabilization mechanisms under SelfStabilizationProperty. A fully homogeneous population (all agents sharing the same value on some heterogeneity axis) cannot engage the autocatalytic loop that HOA maintenance requires: cycle members with identical profiles cannot reinforce differentiated edges. Every maintenance theorem's `feedbackEngaged` premise becomes unsatisfiable, so no maintenance guarantee applies. All three Hook 3 heterogeneity axes named in the source note are formalized: CouplingWeightVector (§HM22), LifeCyclePhase (§HM23), ManifoldShape (§HM24). Each axis gets its own Population-homogeneous predicate, two-axiom mechanism (`*_no_feedback` + `hoaMove_preserves_*Homogeneity`), and derived fragility theorem — nine core Lean ids across the three sections. Load-bearing `*_no_feedback` axioms are undischarged — direct derivation from population-level manifold-overlap dynamics is analogous scope to (B''), not attempted. Falsifiable: peer with agent-heterogeneity toggle testing homogeneous populations for HOA persistence directly tests the axioms. Lean per axis: (attribute-association axiom, Population*Homogeneous predicate, *homogeneous_no_feedback axiom, hoaMove_preserves_*Homogeneity axiom, hoaFragility*Homogeneous theorem). ManifoldShape adds a fresh opaque type `ManifoldShape : Type` (absent from Core.lean). See obsidian/SCORE/emergence/mechanism/AgentHomogeneityFragility.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#HumanCommunity -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#HumanCommunity"/>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#Incorporation -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#Incorporation">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Morphism"/>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#Inscription -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#Inscription">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Morphism"/>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#B1ReferentialInscription -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#B1ReferentialInscription">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Inscription"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Inscription whose content is about B1 world-states (alarm calls, trails, records of events). The B3 floor; available to many A-actors. Referent typing (foundational, 2026-06-04); see domains/B3-Inscription.md the referent axis.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#B2ReferentialInscription -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#B2ReferentialInscription">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Inscription"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#B1ReferentialInscription"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Inscription whose content is about features of the agent's own B2 manifold with no B1 referent (beliefs, self-model, abstractions, shared fictions). Requires sufficient reflexive depth (see the referent GCI in General axioms); the human differentia from which the higher B3 strata, Sigma-actors, and cultural evolution follow.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#LossFunction -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#LossFunction"/>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#LossFunctionContent -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#LossFunctionContent">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#B3_Inscription"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#TelosBearingContent"/>
        <rdfs:comment>B3 content produced via Omega-actor optimization (B1→B3 path). No telos; not subject to Transformation morphism; systematic bias not correctable by social contestation.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#Morphism -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#Morphism"/>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#OmegaActor -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#OmegaActor">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Actor"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Class>
                <owl:complementOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#SigmaActor"/>
            </owl:Class>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#operatesVia"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#LossFunction"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <!-- Fidelity fix (2026-06-03): removed the prior
             `hasReflexiveDepth allValuesFrom ShallowDepth` restriction. Reflexive depth is
             a B2-grounded scale; placing the Omega-actor on it (even vacuously) invited the
             category error the vault guardrail warns against. The A/Σ/Ω disjointness in the
             General axioms below carries the distinction. See agents/ReflexiveDepth.md
             (Omega guardrail) and emergence/cases/AI-StructuralBreak.md. -->
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#Perception -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#Perception">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Morphism"/>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#ReflexiveDepthLevel -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#ReflexiveDepthLevel"/>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#ShallowDepth -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#ShallowDepth">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#ReflexiveDepthLevel"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#SufficientDepth"/>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#SigmaActor -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#SigmaActor">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Actor"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#HigherOrderAgent"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#formedBy"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#CoInscriptionEvent"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#hasReflexiveDepth"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#SufficientDepth"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#inscribesTo"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#TelosBearingContent"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#maintainedBy"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#HumanCommunity"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#SufficientDepth -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#SufficientDepth">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#ReflexiveDepthLevel"/>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#TelosBearingContent -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#TelosBearingContent">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#B3_Inscription"/>
        <rdfs:comment>B3 content produced via B2→B3 Inscription morphism. Bears a telos — subject to social contestation and the Transformation morphism.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#Transformation -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#Transformation">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Morphism"/>
        <rdfs:comment>5th morphism: domain is B2 × B3, range is B3. Role occupants apply existing inscription to new cases, extending B3 content. Binary domain not expressible in OWL; Lean encoding pending (no transform axiom yet in formal/Formal/Score/).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#MeasurementModel -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#MeasurementModel">
        <rdfs:comment>Abstract slot (RefinementArchitecture): the attractor-health measurement model each SCORE implementation specifies. Domain-general as a *role*; concrete metrics are implementation refinements (e.g. polaris:SEWI in score-polaris.owl). No domain-general metric belongs in core.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#FitnessCriterion -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#FitnessCriterion">
        <rdfs:comment>Abstract slot (RefinementArchitecture Q3 promotion, 2026-06-04): the NS fitness criterion each SCORE implementation specifies — the selection pressure determining which HOA cycles persist. Promoted from doc-slot to OWL class on the POLARIS ∩ ETHOS intersection (first on-demand Q3 event). Concrete criteria are implementation refinements (e.g. polaris:InscriptionDynamics, ethos:FloridiInformationHealth). No domain-general criterion belongs in core.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#InterventionClass -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#InterventionClass">
        <rdfs:comment>The SCORE intervention operator taxonomy. Domain-general (a claim about agents), promoted to core from formal/Formal/Score/Core.lean (inductive Intervention). Ordering by activation energy and the somatic filter-bypass of create_rhythm are ordinal/relational facts carried in Lean (activationEnergy, rhythm_lower_energy_than_node), not DL-expressible here.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#CreateRhythm -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#CreateRhythm">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#InterventionClass"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Low activation energy; the only operator that bypasses the perceptual filter, via the somatic channel (embodied synchrony precedes filtering). Lean: Intervention.createRhythm.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#CreateEdge -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#CreateEdge">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#InterventionClass"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Medium activation energy; partial filter bypass through repeated contact. Lean: Intervention.createEdge.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#CreateNode -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#CreateNode">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#InterventionClass"/>
        <rdfs:comment>High activation energy; subject to full perceptual filtering; requires explicit participation. Lean: Intervention.createNode.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#SigmaInterventionClass -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#SigmaInterventionClass">
        <rdfs:comment>The Sigma-actor intervention operator taxonomy: structural operators on a Sigma-actor's formal/informal closure, not on individual-agent coupling. Q3 PROMOTE (2026-06-04, second on-demand event) from the AGORA n ETHOS intersection — both Sigma-actor-level peers need it; the gap was pre-registered by ETHOS (score-ethos.owl) when its structural/ownership operators did not fit the A-actor InterventionClass. A SIBLING of InterventionClass, not a subclass: the two taxonomies act at different actor strata, and a forced common parent would be premature abstraction (RefinementArchitecture no-premature-abstraction rule). Morphism-routing per operator and relative activation energies are not DL-expressible; carried in SigmaActorArchitecture.md S 5.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#InstitutionalDesign -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#InstitutionalDesign">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#SigmaInterventionClass"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Modifies a Sigma-actor's internal coupling topology — constitutional/institutional design operators: supermajority gates, tenure protection, independent appointment commissions, distributed-authority centrality reduction. Changes the attractor structure of the collective manifold rather than individual coupling. See ManifoldCompatibilityDesign.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#DisruptRhythm -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#DisruptRhythm">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#InterventionClass"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Subtractive dual of CreateRhythm: removes an entrainment pattern. Bypasses the perceptual filter for the same reason its dual does - the somatic channel precedes filtering, and no agent need assent to stop being entrained. Lean: Intervention.disruptRhythm. Added 2026-07-19 (audit item VC-1). NOTE: the activation-energy ordering does NOT extend to the subtractive family; Lean activationEnergy is deliberately undefined (none) there.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#SeverEdge -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#SeverEdge">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#InterventionClass"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Subtractive dual of CreateEdge: removes connectivity between existing nodes. Lean: Intervention.severEdge. Added 2026-07-19 (audit item VC-1).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#DissolveNode -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#DissolveNode">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#InterventionClass"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Subtractive dual of CreateNode: removes organizational structure. Takes no seed size - that is a creation parameter; dissolution cost is governed by the target's accumulated persistence stack (Hysteresis's three mechanisms in window-width order), not by a quantity of the operator. Lean: Intervention.dissolveNode. Added 2026-07-19 (audit item VC-1).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#InterSigmaCoupling -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#InterSigmaCoupling">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#SigmaInterventionClass"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Creates or dissolves formal coupling between Sigma-actors: treaty formation, alliance, sanctions, diplomatic recognition. The Sigma-actor-level analog of create_edge. See SigmaActorArchitecture.md S 2 (inter-Sigma coupling criterion).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#FoundingConditionIntervention -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#FoundingConditionIntervention">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#SigmaInterventionClass"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Influences the founding B3 of a nascent Sigma-actor at the crystallization moment (the CoInscriptionEvent). Highest-leverage, longest-lasting Sigma-intervention; the Sigma-actor-level analog of childhood inscription influence. See SigmaActorArchitecture.md (formation; lifecycle).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#CollectiveManifoldShift -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#CollectiveManifoldShift">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#SigmaInterventionClass"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Operations that shift a Sigma-actor's effective collective manifold toward or away from B1 accuracy: institutional reform, leadership-succession engineering, information operations (disruption pole); automatic correction triggers that act on the maintaining community without the captured comparator (restoration pole). See HighCentralityDisruption.md (Mechanism 1) and SigmaActorArchitecture.md S 1a.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#AdjacentPossibleConstraint -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#AdjacentPossibleConstraint">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#SigmaInterventionClass"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Fifth Sigma-intervention operator (Q3 PROMOTE, 2026-06-04, fifth on-demand event, ATLAS n NEXUS intersection). Operates on the structural possibility space directly — infrastructure / supply-chain / technology control — opening or closing behavioral paths regardless of the target's manifold or coupling. The least reflexive-depth-dependent operator (no model of the target is needed, only their structural dependencies). ATLAS surfaced it (blockade / supply-chain interdiction / technology denial; NAryDeterrence); NEXUS was the second peer (kill zones = adjacent-possible contraction; antitrust / commons / NS-restoration = the reopening operators). See ATLAS.md, NEXUS.md, InnovationEcosystem.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#PathologicalAttractor -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#PathologicalAttractor">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#HigherOrderAgent"/>
        <rdfs:comment>The captured-closure failure mode (Q3 PROMOTE, 2026-06-04, fourth on-demand event). A HigherOrderAgent whose coupling density persists (or grows) but whose operative FitnessCriterion has been captured to preserve the incumbent closure rather than satisfy the domain fitness. Discriminated from genuine (generative) closure by Deacon's net-information-increase criterion: genuine constraint closure EXPANDS the adjacent possible (adds absent possibilities); a pathological attractor is self-maintaining but anti-generative — it CONTRACTS the adjacent possible (the kill zone removes reachable configurations). The general form, shared across POLARIS (high SEWI + repudiated social contract), ETHOS (captured epistemic NS), ATLAS (corporate NS-as-cartel), and NEXUS (kill-zone cartel). The expand-vs-contract discriminant is dynamical and DL-inexpressible; see InnovationEcosystem.md "Formalizing NS as cartel" and HOA.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- ── Collective-manifold-update operator (Q3 PROMOTE, 2026-06-18, sixth on-demand event) ──
         The Sigma-actor processing-chain step by which a SigmaActor updates its effective
         collective manifold from a received percept — the long under-specified
         collective-manifold-update step (SigmaActorArchitecture S 1-2). Promoted on the
         AGORA n ATLAS intersection: AGORA needs it for captured correction
         (agora:CapturedCorrectionUpdate), ATLAS for coverage-distorted signal reception
         (atlas:CoverageModulatedReception). Distinct from the SigmaInterventionClass
         CollectiveManifoldShift, which is the INTERVENTION that drives such an update; this is
         the update mechanism itself. Dynamical content (the captured-only mismatch floor + the
         necessity of an independent correcting node; the multiplicative coverage x reflexive-depth
         fidelity decay) is DL-inexpressible — see the modular Lean spine (formal/Formal/Score/)
         (captured_correction_needs_independent_node, low_coverage_compounds_with_reflexive_depth)
         and AGORA-CollectiveManifoldUpdate.md / ATLAS-SignalingCascade.md. -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#CollectiveManifoldUpdate -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#CollectiveManifoldUpdate">
        <rdfs:comment>The Sigma-actor collective-manifold-update operator: the process by which a SigmaActor updates its effective collective manifold from a received percept. Q3 PROMOTE (2026-06-18, sixth on-demand event, AGORA n ATLAS intersection) — the under-specified collective-manifold-update step of the Sigma-actor processing chain. Filled by agora:CapturedCorrectionUpdate (update under captured correction) and atlas:CoverageModulatedReception (update under a coverage-distorted percept). Distinct from the intervention CollectiveManifoldShift (which drives an update); this is the update mechanism. Dynamical content is DL-inexpressible; see formal/Formal/Score/Agora.lean and Atlas.lean.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- ── Adjacent-possible (captured-NS) measure (Q3 PROMOTE, 2026-06-18, seventh on-demand event) ──
         The expand-vs-contract (Deacon net-information-increase) discriminant: the operational
         measure of whether a closure EXPANDS or CONTRACTS the adjacent possible — the operational
         face of core:PathologicalAttractor (DOEEvaluation S 4.5, giving that class operational
         teeth). Promoted on the NEXUS n ETHOS intersection: NEXUS measures it as kill-zone
         adjacent-possible contraction (nexus:KillZoneExtent), ETHOS as amplification-quality
         decoupling (ethos:CaptureDiscriminant, kappa = cov(a,Q)). The numeric forms (Phi, delta,
         cov(a,Q)) are Q4 BIND; the antitone-under-contraction structure is in formal/Formal/Score/Nexus.lean
         (contraction_is_antitone_in_adjacent_possible). -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#AdjacentPossibleMeasure -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#AdjacentPossibleMeasure">
        <rdfs:comment>The captured-NS measure: the expand-vs-contract discriminant (Deacon net-information-increase) detecting whether a HigherOrderAgent's closure expands the adjacent possible (generative) or contracts it (a core:PathologicalAttractor). Q3 PROMOTE (2026-06-18, seventh on-demand event, NEXUS n ETHOS intersection) — the operational face of PathologicalAttractor (DOEEvaluation S 4.5). Filled by nexus:KillZoneExtent (adjacent-possible contraction via defensive acquisition) and ethos:CaptureDiscriminant (amplification decoupled from content quality). Numeric Phi/delta/cov(a,Q) are Q4 BIND; the antitone-under-contraction structure is in formal/Formal/Score/Nexus.lean. The one domain-general MEASURE admitted to core, justified by the >=2-peer intersection (cf. the MeasurementModel slot comment: domain-specific health metrics stay in impl layers).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#DoctrinalRegion -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#DoctrinalRegion">
        <rdfs:comment>A community's region R(C): the graded down-set of the doctrinallyComposesFrom DAG that a community co-inscribes / maintains — the formal home of "a community's shared B3" (the derived B3 community fibration; B3CommunityFibration.md, B3RegionGeometry.md). Q3 PROMOTE (2026-06-21, eighth on-demand event, ETHOS n NEXUS intersection): ETHOS fills it with ethos:DisciplinaryCorpus (a discipline's citation corpus), NEXUS with nexus:ParadigmCluster (a patent-citation paradigm cluster). DERIVED over the single B3 — a structure of regions OVER B3_Inscription, never a re-typing of it; the primitive B3 stays a shared singleton. The down-closure law and the graded-product geometry (a region is a down-set, graded by the emergence hierarchy, generated by its frontier) are DL-inexpressible; carried in formal/Formal/Score/Core.lean (IsRegion, downClosure_isRegion, region_substrate_closed_and_graded) and B3RegionGeometry.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



    <!-- ════════════ Trace + open (n-branch) trace-processor taxonomy ════════════
         Promote-by-nature (2026-07-02): the domain-general object of dynamical analysis (a
         time-ordered system-state record, from measurement or simulation) and an OPEN taxonomy of
         operators over it. Two branches are instantiated by live workstreams (time-domain / CSP via
         FDR4; transform-domain via the Segment 6 spectral layer). Generality is external
         (dynamical-systems theory; Scheffer 2009), not a >=2-peer intersection — the InterventionClass
         precedent. The taxonomy is deliberately OPEN: NO covering / disjoint-union axiom on
         TraceProcessor, so further modes (statistical, topological, symbolic-dynamics) are additions,
         not edits. See obsidian/SCORE/measurement/{Trace,SpectralEarlyWarningIndicator}.md. -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#Trace -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#Trace">
        <rdfs:label>Trace</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>A time-ordered record of a system's state or events, produced by measurement (empirical series) or simulation (trajectory ensemble) and consumed by the analysis layers. Source-agnostic and domain-general — the substrate on which all dynamical analysis operates. See Trace.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#TraceProcessor -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#TraceProcessor">
        <rdfs:label>Trace processor</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>An operator over a Trace (core:processes). The taxonomy of processing MODES is deliberately OPEN (n branches): TimeDomainProcessor and TransformDomainProcessor are the first two, instantiated by live workstreams; no covering axiom closes the class, so further modes are admitted as subclasses. Broader than MeasurementModel — a processor's output may be a measurement (SpectralEarlyWarningIndicator) or a verification verdict (CSP refinement). See Trace.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#TimeDomainProcessor -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#TimeDomainProcessor">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#TraceProcessor"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#TransformDomainProcessor"/>
        <rdfs:label>Time-domain processor</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Processes a Trace as a sequence in the time/event domain: refinement, failures, divergences (CSP-like trace semantics). Instantiated by the FDR4 CSPm protocol-verification track; TN-7 is a shelved POLARIS application. Formalization deferred (FDR4 is external). Disjoint from TransformDomainProcessor (distinct modes), but the two do NOT cover TraceProcessor.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#TransformDomainProcessor -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#TransformDomainProcessor">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#TraceProcessor"/>
        <rdfs:label>Transform-domain processor</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Processes a Trace by applying a transform (Fourier, wavelet) then computing indicators. Instantiated by the Segment 6 spectral layer (PSD, wavelet, coherence, SEWI). First worked filler: SpectralEarlyWarningIndicator.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/core#SpectralEarlyWarningIndicator -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/core#SpectralEarlyWarningIndicator">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#TransformDomainProcessor"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#MeasurementModel"/>
        <rdfs:label>Spectral early-warning indicator</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>A baseline-standardized indicator of proximity to a bifurcation, computed from critical-slowing-down signatures (variance, autocorrelation, spectral-centroid) of the Fourier representation of a Trace. Domain-general by nature (Scheffer et al. 2009); promoted by-nature on a single filler (polaris:SEWI), the taxonomy's openness containing the POLARIS-shaped-core risk. Both a TransformDomainProcessor (the computation) and a MeasurementModel (the resulting measure). The generic monotonicity property (nondecreasing in each critical-slowing-down signature) is Lean spectral_ews_monotone (lean-planned). polaris:SEWI SPECIALIZEs it. See SpectralEarlyWarningIndicator.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>



